nds sequentially. Allows combining log file and webhook backends.\n\n**Log File Backend:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/plugin/pkg/audit/log/backend.go:NewBackend` - Creates a log file backend that writes audit events to a file.\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/plugin/pkg/audit/log/backend.go:ProcessEvents` - Encodes and writes events in either legacy (1-line text) or JSON format.\n\n**Webhook Backend:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/plugin/pkg/audit/webhook/webhook.go:NewBackend` - Creates a webhook backend configured from a file.\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/plugin/pkg/audit/webhook/webhook.go:NewDynamicBackend` - Creates a webhook backend from a REST client for dynamic webhook configuration.\n- The webhook backend sends audit events via HTTP POST requests to external audit services with exponential backoff retry logic.\n\n**Buffered Backend (Event Batching):**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/plugin/pkg/audit/buffered/buffered.go:NewBackend` - Wraps a delegate backend with buffering and batching capabilities.\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/plugin/pkg/audit/buffered/buffered.go:ProcessEvents` - Collects events into batches and sends them to the delegate backend asynchronously or synchronously based on configuration. Supports batching modes (batch, blocking, blocking-strict) with throttling.\n\n## 4. Audit Truncation for Large Events\n\nThe truncation system prevents oversized events from being lost:\n\n**Truncation Backend:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/plugin/pkg/audit/truncate/truncate.go:NewBackend` - Creates a truncating backend that wraps a delegate backend.\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/plugin/pkg/audit/truncate/truncate.go:ProcessEvents` - Checks event size and batch size against configured limits. If an event exceeds MaxEventSize, it calls the truncate() function.\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/plugin/pkg/audit/truncate/truncate.go:truncate` - Removes RequestObject and ResponseObject from oversized events while preserving metadata. Adds an annotation 'audit.k8s.io/truncated: true' to indicate truncation.\n\n## 5. Audit Configuration & Wiring\n\nThe server options package assembles and configures all audit components:\n\n**Audit Options:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/options/audit.go:AuditOptions` - Configuration struct for audit settings (policy file, log options, webhook options).\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/options/audit.go:AuditLogOptions` - Configuration for log file backend (path, max age, max backups, format, batching, truncation).\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/options/audit.go:AuditWebhookOptions` - Configuration for webhook backend (config file, retry backoff, batching, truncation).\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/options/audit.go:AuditBatchOptions` - Configuration for batching mode (batch size, max wait, throttling).\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/options/audit.go:AuditTruncateOptions` - Configuration for event truncation (enabled flag, max event size, max batch size).\n\n**Backend Assembly:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/options/audit.go:ApplyTo` - Main method that assembles the complete audit system:\n  1. Creates the policy rule evaluator from the policy file\n  2. Creates the log backend (if enabled)\n  3. Creates the webhook backend (if enabled)\n  4. Wraps the webhook backend with truncation and buffering\n  5. Combines backends using the Union function\n  6. Sets the AuditBackend and AuditPolicyRuleEvaluator in the server config\n\n**Policy Loading:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/options/audit.go:newPolicyRuleEvaluator` - Loads policy from file and creates a policy evaluator.\n\n## 6. Audit Event Types\n\n**Internal API Types:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/apis/audit/types.go` - Internal audit event types including Event struct with stage, level, user info, object references, request/response objects.\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/apis/audit/v1/types.go` - v1 audit event schema for serialization.\n\n## Complete Request Flow\n\n1. **WithAuditInit** initializes the audit context and generates/receives an audit ID\n2. **WithAudit** decorator intercepts the request\n3. **evaluatePolicyAndCreateAuditEvent** evaluates the policy and initializes the audit context\n4. **LogRequestMetadata** captures request details\n5. At each stage (RequestReceived, ResponseStarted, ResponseComplete), **ProcessEventStage** sends the event to the backend(s)\n6. **Union** backend optionally routes to multiple backends\n7. **Truncate** backend checks size and truncates if needed\n8. **Buffered** backend batches events before dispatching\n9. **Log** and **Webhook** backends process the final events\n\nThis architecture provides flexible, scalable audit logging with policy-based filtering, multiple output formats, and automatic event truncation for large payloads."
}

